<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1930,2031]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,152,1410]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[151,395,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Colour of macerated, slide-mounted females yellow, with abdomen faintly shaded medially and antecostal ridges darker; antennal segments III–V darker in apical third, VI–VII light brown; forewings pale to weakly shaded. Antennae 
<number box="[706,720,2005,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="7.0">7</number>
-segmented. Ocellar setae III small, shorter than distance between hind ocelli, just behind first ocellus and within or on margins of ocellar triangle (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1299,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1266,1299,152,178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum transversely striate, with about 
<number box="[525,554,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="30.0">30</number>
discal setae; anterior margin with about 
<number box="[1043,1058,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
pairs of setae, posterior margin with 
<number box="[211,226,226,252]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.0">3</number>
(or 
<number box="[275,291,226,252]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="4.0">4</number>
) pairs between the posteroangular setae. Mesonotum without anterior campaniform sensilla (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,187,264,290]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metanotum closely striate laterally, with widely spaced transverse lines in front of median setae, sculpture varying posteromedially from closely striate to narrow elongate reticulation; campaniform sensilla absent (
<figureCitation box="[249,343,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[308,343,338,364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing first vein with 
<number box="[681,727,338,364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9</number>
setae on distal half; clavus with 
<number box="[1143,1158,338,364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
(or 
<number box="[1212,1228,338,364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
) marginal setae. Abdominal tergites with a few sculpture lines extending to median setae and campaniform sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1422,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1422,376,402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergite II with 
<number box="[318,333,413,439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.0">3</number>
lateral marginal setae; ctenidia present on V–VIII; comb on VIII long and slender; IX with no anterior campaniform sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[554,652,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,652,450,476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
); pleurotergites with no discal setae, with many rows of fine microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[310,397,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Thrips species. kurahashii 24 – 27: (24) head &amp; pronotum; (25) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (26) tergite VIII; (27) sternites V – VI. Thrips meruensis male 28 – 30: (28) head; (29) mesonotum &amp; metanotum; (30) pronotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194535/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[364,397,488,514]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sternites III–VII with 
<number box="[676,749,488,514]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="18.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="16.0">16–20</number>
discal setae placed irregularly, on III–VI some of these are close to posterior margin; sternite II with about 
<number box="[710,725,525,551]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.0">3</number>
discal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1410]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Measurements (
<typeStatus box="[385,489,562,588]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
female in microns). Body length 
<number box="[889,951,562,588]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1270.0">1270</number>
. Head, length 
<number box="[1122,1155,562,588]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="90.0">90</number>
; width across eyes 
<number box="[1383,1430,562,588]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="145.0">145</number>
; ocellar setae 
<date box="[312,390,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
III 
<number box="[351,385,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="15.0">15</number>
.
</date>
Pronotum, length 
<number box="[619,667,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="115.0">115</number>
; width 
<number box="[758,807,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="175.0">175</number>
; posteroangular setae 
<number box="[1080,1160,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="30.35">30, 35</number>
. Forewing length 
<number box="[1383,1433,600,626]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="750.0">750</number>
. Antennal segments III–VII length 
<number box="[554,630,637,663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="45.4">45, 40</number>
, 
<number box="[642,718,637,663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="32.48">32, 48</number>
, 
<number box="[730,762,637,663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="15.0">15</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1410]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[198,258,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male</emphasis>
. Similar to female but smaller; pleurotergal microtrichia more irregular on sculpture lines; tergite VIII posteromarginal comb reduced to 
<number box="[618,633,712,738]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
long microtrichia medially, none laterally; tergite IX setal pairs S 
<number box="[1424,1436,712,738]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.0">1</number>
and S 
<number box="[216,231,749,775]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2.0">2</number>
with bases arranged almost in straight line; sternites IV–V with slender, transverse pore plate.
</paragraph>
