<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1410]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[198,322,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Comments</emphasis>
. The pleurotergal microtrichia of females of this species are rather similar to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabaci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Thrips tabaci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a character state also shared with 
<taxonomicName box="[629,756,1123,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speratus">
<emphasis box="[629,756,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. speratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and to a lesser extent with some specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1428,1123,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acaciae">
<emphasis box="[1309,1428,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. acaciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, although closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[617,753,1160,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speratus">
<emphasis box="[617,753,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">T. speratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this new species is readily distinguished by the larger number of setae on the forewing first vein, and also by the other character states indicated in the key above. The specimens on which this description was initially based were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1227,1234,1260]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">South Africa</collectingCountry>
by H. Kurahashi, a quarantine officer from 
<collectingCountry box="[455,525,1272,1298]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and kindly submitted for study by Kazushige Minoura of the Japanese Plant Protection service. Subsequently, Sverre Kobro sent further slides of the same species, and these are included here as 
<typeStatus box="[250,376,1346,1372]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratypes</typeStatus>
. One of the four females he collected at Cape Town has on the metanotum a single campaniform sensillum, whereas all of the other available specimens lack such a structure on the metanotum.
</paragraph>
